   1:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c **** /**
   2:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   ******************************************************************************
   3:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   * @file    stm324x9i_eval_sdio_sd.c
   4:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   * @author  MCD Application Team
   5:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   * @version V1.0.3
   6:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   * @date    13-November-2013
   7:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   * @brief   This file provides a set of functions needed to manage the SDIO SD 
   8:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          Card memory mounted on STM324x9I-EVAL evaluation board. 
   9:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          
  10:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *            
  11:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *  @verbatim
  12:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  13:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          ===================================================================
  14:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                                   How to use this driver
  15:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          ===================================================================
  16:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          It implements a high level communication layer for read and write 
  17:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          from/to this memory. The needed STM32 hardware resources (SDIO and 
  18:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          GPIO) are defined in stm324x9i_eval.h file, and the initialization is 
  19:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          performed in SD_LowLevel_Init() function declared in stm324x9i_eval.c 
  20:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          file.
  21:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          You can easily tailor this driver to any other development board, 
  22:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          by just adapting the defines for hardware resources and 
  23:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          SD_LowLevel_Init() function.
  24:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  25:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          A - SD Card Initialization and configuration
  26:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          ============================================    
  27:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *            - To initialize the SD Card, use the SD_Init() function.  It 
  28:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              Initializes the SD Card and put it into StandBy State (Ready 
  29:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              for data transfer). This function provides the following operations:
  30:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  31:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              1 - Apply the SD Card initialization process at 400KHz and check
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccRomHfZ.s 			page 2


  32:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  the SD Card type (Standard Capacity or High Capacity). You 
  33:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  can change or adapt this frequency by adjusting the 
  34:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  "SDIO_INIT_CLK_DIV" define inside the stm324x9i_eval.h file. 
  35:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  The SD Card frequency (SDIO_CK) is computed as follows:
  36:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  37:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                     +---------------------------------------------+
  38:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                     | SDIO_CK = SDIOCLK / (SDIO_INIT_CLK_DIV + 2) |
  39:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                     +---------------------------------------------+
  40:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  41:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  In initialization mode and according to the SD Card standard, 
  42:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  make sure that the SDIO_CK frequency doesn't exceed 400KHz.
  43:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  44:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              2 - Get the SD CID and CSD data. All these information are
  45:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  managed by the SDCardInfo structure. This structure provides
  46:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  also ready computed SD Card capacity and Block size.   
  47:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  48:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              3 - Configure the SD Card Data transfer frequency. By Default,
  49:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  the card transfer frequency is set to 24MHz. You can change
  50:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  or adapt this frequency by adjusting the "SDIO_TRANSFER_CLK_DIV" 
  51:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  define inside the stm324x9i_eval.h file.
  52:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  The SD Card frequency (SDIO_CK) is computed as follows:
  53:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  54:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                     +---------------------------------------------+
  55:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                     | SDIO_CK = SDIOCLK / (SDIO_INIT_CLK_DIV + 2) |
  56:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                     +---------------------------------------------+
  57:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  58:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  In transfer mode and according to the SD Card standard, 
  59:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  make sure that the SDIO_CK frequency doesn't exceed 25MHz
  60:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  and 50MHz in High-speed mode switch.
  61:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  To be able to use a frequency higher than 24MHz, you should
  62:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  use the SDIO peripheral in bypass mode. Refer to the 
  63:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                  corresponding reference manual for more details.
  64:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  65:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              4 -  Select the corresponding SD Card according to the address
  66:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                   read with the step 2.
  67:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  68:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              5 -  Configure the SD Card in wide bus mode: 4-bits data.
  69:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  70:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          B - SD Card Read operation
  71:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          ========================== 
  72:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - You can read SD card by using two functions : SD_ReadBlock() and
  73:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             SD_ReadMultiBlocks() functions. These functions support only
  74:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             512-byte block length.
  75:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - The SD_ReadBlock() function reads only one block (512-byte). This
  76:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             function can transfer the data using DMA controller or using 
  77:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             polling mode. To select between DMA or polling mode refer to 
  78:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             "SD_DMA_MODE" or "SD_POLLING_MODE" inside the stm324x9i_eval_sdio_sd.h
  79:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             file and uncomment the corresponding line. By default the SD DMA
  80:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             mode is selected          
  81:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - The SD_ReadMultiBlocks() function reads only mutli blocks (multiple 
  82:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             of 512-byte). 
  83:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - Any read operation should be followed by two functions to check
  84:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             if the DMA Controller and SD Card status.
  85:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              - SD_ReadWaitOperation(): this function insure that the DMA
  86:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                controller has finished all data transfer.
  87:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              - SD_GetStatus(): to check that the SD Card has finished the 
  88:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                data transfer and it is ready for data.
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccRomHfZ.s 			page 3


  89:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  90:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - The DMA transfer is finished by the SDIO Data End interrupt. 
  91:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             User has to call the SD_ProcessIRQ() function inside the SDIO_IRQHandler()
  92:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             and SD_ProcessDMAIRQ() function inside the DMA2_Streamx_IRQHandler().
  93:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Don't forget to enable the SDIO_IRQn and DMA2_Stream3_IRQn or 
  94:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             DMA2_Stream6_IRQn interrupts using the NVIC controller.
  95:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
  96:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          C - SD Card Write operation
  97:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          =========================== 
  98:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - You can write SD card by using two function: SD_WriteBlock() and
  99:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             SD_WriteMultiBlocks() functions. These functions support only
 100:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             512-byte block length.   
 101:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - The SD_WriteBlock() function write only one block (512-byte). This
 102:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             function can transfer the data using DMA controller or using 
 103:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             polling mode. To select between DMA or polling mode refer to 
 104:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             "SD_DMA_MODE" or "SD_POLLING_MODE" inside the stm324x9i_eval_sdio_sd.h
 105:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             file and uncomment the corresponding line. By default the SD DMA
 106:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             mode is selected          
 107:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - The SD_WriteMultiBlocks() function write only mutli blocks (multiple 
 108:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             of 512-byte). 
 109:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - Any write operation should be followed by two functions to check
 110:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             if the DMA Controller and SD Card status.
 111:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              - SD_ReadWaitOperation(): this function insure that the DMA
 112:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                controller has finished all data transfer.
 113:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *              - SD_GetStatus(): to check that the SD Card has finished the 
 114:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                data transfer and it is ready for data.
 115:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 116:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - The DMA transfer is finished by the SDIO Data End interrupt. 
 117:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             User has to call the SD_ProcessIRQ() function inside the SDIO_IRQHandler()
 118:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             and SD_ProcessDMAIRQ() function inside the DMA2_Streamx_IRQHandler().
 119:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Don't forget to enable the SDIO_IRQn and DMA2_Stream3_IRQn or 
 120:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             DMA2_Stream6_IRQn interrupts using the NVIC controller.
 121:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 122:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 123:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          D - SD card status
 124:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          ================== 
 125:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - At any time, you can check the SD Card status and get the SD card
 126:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             state by using the SD_GetStatus() function. This function checks
 127:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             first if the SD card is still connected and then get the internal
 128:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             SD Card transfer state.     
 129:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *           - You can also get the SD card SD Status register by using the 
 130:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             SD_SendSDStatus() function.
 131:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 132:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          E - Programming Model (Selecting DMA for SDIO data Transfer)
 133:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          ============================================================ 
 134:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Status = SD_Init(); // Initialization Step as described in section A
 135:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 136:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             // SDIO Interrupt ENABLE
 137:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             NVIC_InitStructure.NVIC_IRQChannel = SDIO_IRQn;
 138:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             NVIC_InitStructure.NVIC_IRQChannelPreemptionPriority = 0;
 139:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             NVIC_InitStructure.NVIC_IRQChannelSubPriority = 0;
 140:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             NVIC_InitStructure.NVIC_IRQChannelCmd = ENABLE;
 141:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             NVIC_Init(&NVIC_InitStructure);
 142:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             // DMA2 STREAMx Interrupt ENABLE
 143:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             NVIC_InitStructure.NVIC_IRQChannel = SD_SDIO_DMA_IRQn;
 144:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             NVIC_InitStructure.NVIC_IRQChannelPreemptionPriority = 1;
 145:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             NVIC_Init(&NVIC_InitStructure);
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccRomHfZ.s 			page 4


 146:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *               
 147:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             // Write operation as described in Section C
 148:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Status = SD_WriteBlock(buffer, address, 512);
 149:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Status = SD_WaitWriteOperation();
 150:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             while(SD_GetStatus() != SD_TRANSFER_OK);
 151:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 152:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Status = SD_WriteMultiBlocks(buffer, address, 512, NUMBEROFBLOCKS);
 153:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Status = SD_WaitWriteOperation();
 154:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             while(SD_GetStatus() != SD_TRANSFER_OK);
 155:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 156:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             // Read operation as described in Section B
 157:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Status = SD_ReadBlock(buffer, address, 512);
 158:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Status = SD_WaitReadOperation();
 159:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             while(SD_GetStatus() != SD_TRANSFER_OK);
 160:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 161:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Status = SD_ReadMultiBlocks(buffer, address, 512, NUMBEROFBLOCKS);
 162:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             Status = SD_WaitReadOperation();
 163:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             while(SD_GetStatus() != SD_TRANSFER_OK);
 164:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 165:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *             - Add the SDIO and DMA2 StreamX (3 or 6) IRQ Handlers:   
 166:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                 void SDIO_IRQHandler(void)
 167:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                 {
 168:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                   SD_ProcessIRQ();  
 169:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                 }   
 170:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                 void SD_SDIO_DMA_IRQHANDLER(void)
 171:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                 {
 172:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                   SD_ProcessDMAIRQ();  
 173:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                 }     
 174:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 175:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          F - Programming Model (Selecting Polling for SDIO data Transfer)
 176:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          ================================================================
 177:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *            //Only SD Card Single Block operation are managed.   
 178:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *            Status = SD_Init(); // Initialization Step as described in section
 179:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *               
 180:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *            // Write operation as described in Section C
 181:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *            Status = SD_WriteBlock(buffer, address, 512);
 182:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
 183:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *            // Read operation as described in Section B
 184:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *            Status = SD_ReadBlock(buffer, address, 512);
 185:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *                 
 186:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          STM32 SDIO Pin assignment
 187:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          =========================
 188:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          +-----------------------------------------------------------+
 189:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |                     Pin assignment                        |
 190:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          +-----------------------------+---------------+-------------+
 191:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |  STM32 SDIO Pins            |     SD        |    Pin      |
 192:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          +-----------------------------+---------------+-------------+
 193:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |      SDIO D2                |   D2          |    1        |
 194:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |      SDIO D3                |   D3          |    2        |
 195:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |      SDIO CMD               |   CMD         |    3        |
 196:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |                             |   VCC         |    4 (3.3 V)|
 197:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |      SDIO CLK               |   CLK         |    5        |
 198:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |                             |   GND         |    6 (0 V)  |
 199:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |      SDIO D0                |   D0          |    7        |
 200:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          |      SDIO D1                |   D1          |    8        |
 201:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *          +-----------------------------+---------------+-------------+
 202:MyHardWare/Src/sdio_sd.c ****   *
